section.section:
The Department of State Police shall:
adopt guidelines and develop procedures for issuing a Silver Alert for a missing person;
provide training to local law enforcement agencies on the guidelines and procedures to be used to handle a report of a missing person;
provide assistance to a local law enforcement agency, as necessary, to assist in the safe recovery of a missing person;
recruit public and commercial television and radio broadcasters, local volunteer groups, and other members of the public to assist in developing and implementing a Silver Alert;
consult with the State Highway Administration to establish a plan for providing information relevant to a Silver Alert to the public through the dynamic message sign system located across the State; and
